page.title: 09Shobrooke Park.
page.content: WILDLIFE. Shobrooke Park is a nature reserve for mammals, birds and fish. In the private part of the park foxes, badgers, rabbits and squirrels all live. On the lake swans, cormarants, mallards, shellducks, great crested grebes, coots, moorhens and canadian geese all nest. The birds in the trees are Jackdaws, Rooks, Jays, Herons and Longtailed Tits. In the lake are Tench, Carp Eels and Mirror Carp. PESTS The pests in the park are the squirrels because they eat the shoots of young trees. Canadian Geese are because they eat the grass and damage nearby farmers crops. They also leave their droppings about the place. The other pest is the human being because they vandalise things in the park.
